3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Phemex calculates NEAR/USDT funding rates using a weighted average of the premium between perpetual and mark prices over the previous 8 hours. Funding exchanges occur at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC, with rates typically ranging from -0.01% to 0.375% per interval. Long positions pay funding when rates are positive, while shorts receive payments when rates turn negative."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","NEAR","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"NEAR's moderate trading volume and Layer 1 narrative exposure create periodic funding rate imbalances on Phemex, especially during ecosystem developments or staking yield changes. The pair benefits from Phemex's contract trading specialization while avoiding the extreme volatility of smaller altcoins."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical NEAR Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"NEAR/USDT funding rates on Phemex have historically spiked during major protocol upgrades and DeFi ecosystem growth phases. Rates frequently turn negative during broader market downturns when short interest increases. The 8-hour intervals provide sufficient time for rate convergence, with extreme rates above 0.1% typically correcting within 1-2 funding periods. Weekend funding tends to be more volatile due to reduced arbitrage activity from institutional players."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities and Strategies"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Cross-exchange arbitrage works effectively by comparing Phemex's NEAR funding rates with Binance and OKX rates, which operate on different intervals. Delta-neutral strategies benefit from Phemex's low maker fees when hedging spot NEAR positions against perpetual shorts. The exchange's clean UI enables quick position management during funding rate spikes. Automated strategies should account for Phemex's occasional liquidity gaps during Asian trading hours."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations and Limitations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"NEAR's moderate liquidity on Phemex can lead to slippage during large position entries, particularly outside peak trading hours. The exchange's smaller user base means funding rates may not correct as quickly as on larger platforms. Position sizing should account for potential gaps in order book depth, especially during volatile market conditions. Traders should monitor NEAR's staking unlock schedules and protocol governance events that can impact perpetual-spot price relationships."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"What are typical NEAR funding rates on Phemex?","answer":"NEAR funding rates on Phemex typically range from -0.01% to 0.1% per 8-hour period. During high demand for long positions or ecosystem catalysts, rates can spike to 0.2-0.375%, while bear markets often see sustained negative rates around -0.05%."},{"question":"How does Phemex's 0.01% maker fee affect NEAR funding strategies?","answer":"The low maker fee significantly improves funding rate arbitrage profitability by reducing entry/exit costs. With 8-hour funding intervals, the fee represents only a small fraction of potential funding earnings during high-rate periods, making frequent position adjustments economically viable."},{"question":"What's the minimum position size for NEAR perpetuals on Phemex?","answer":"Phemex requires a minimum order value of $1 for NEAR/USDT perpetuals with 0.001 NEAR minimum quantity increments. The exchange supports up to 50x leverage, though funding rate strategies typically use lower leverage to manage liquidation risk during volatile periods."},{"question":"How reliable is NEAR liquidity on Phemex compared to tier-1 exchanges?","answer":"Phemex's NEAR liquidity is adequate for small to medium-sized funding strategies but can show gaps during off-peak hours. The order book depth typically supports trades up to $10,000 without significant slippage, though larger positions may require splitting across multiple intervals."}]}]
